node.title: Singapore will begin easing its Covid restrictions next week.
node.description: The Southeast Asian city state is recovering from a recent surge of hospitalizations. An official said its reopening would proceed in a “step-by-step manner.”

node.title: Italy prepares for an 18th weekend of demonstrations against the country’s health pass.
node.description: Police officers were out in force to prevent violence and protect shops, with some store owners lamenting that the protests disrupt business.

node.title: US Navy Ship Named After Gay Rights Leader Harvey Milk is Launched in San Diego Bay
node.description: Milk, the first openly gay official to be elected in California in the 1970s, had been forced out of the Navy because of his sexual orientation.

node.title: 14 of the 16 Most Popular Governors Are Republicans
node.description: GOP governors leading Democratic-leaning states earned especially high marks from voters, a new poll found.

node.title: Pence Vows to Back GOP Governors Facing Trump-Approved Challengers
node.description: "I want to be clear," the former vice president reportedly told GOP governors in private. "I'm going to be supporting incumbent Republican governors."

node.title: Thousands in Vienna protest Austria's looming lockdown
node.description: The far-right opposition Freedom Party was among those who have called for the protest and vowed to combat the new restrictions.
